\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{n}\delta(\vec{x}''-\vec{x}_{n})$
\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 equally-spaced points 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{x}_{n}$
\end_inset

 around the circle, with unknown amplitudes 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{n}$
\end_inset

, and we will enforce the Dirichlet boundary condition approximately, only
 at another set of 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 points 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{y}_{m}$
\end_inset

 that are halfway in between the 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{x}_{n}$
\end_inset

 points.
 (Caveat: there are much better ways to set up this approximation in a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

serious
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 calculation; these are generally called NystrÃ¶m methods.) This is shown
